The paper deals with multiagent reinforcement learning (MARL) in robotic systems, which involves learning a communication graph among agents. This falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and multiagent systems (cs.MA). Given that the paper focuses on learning a sparse communication graph, which is a common problem in machine learning, cs.LG is the most likely category. However, since the paper also deals with robotic systems, cs.RO is also a likely category. The other categories are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
